post_text: Our construction partner @KnutsonConstruction carefully replanted Central Middle School staff member memorial trees around the property prior to beginning any construction at Central Middle School. These trees are in memory of CMS staff members Cherie Hansen, Marty Paulsen, Barb Swanson, Joe Epping, Paula Epping and Rosemary Daley. Our community remembers these staff members lost too soon during their time with Eden Prairie Schools. The construction at Central Middle School is part of the May 2019 voter approved referendum to unite 6th graders with their middle school peers in the fall of 2021. #weinspireeach

post_text: Since 2005, My Book Day has been a tradition for first grade students in Eden Prairie in collaboration with the Eden Prairie Noon Rotary. This year we celebrated in a different way, creating My Book Week. The team delivered a book to the home of each of Eden Prairie Schools' 620 first graders, and shared online videos from EPHS students, Eden Prairie government officials, community members and Eden Prairie Schools staff about the importance of reading.

post_text: Eagle Zone staff have been providing child care for families of healthcare workers and emergency personnel since March 16. Many social distancing measures have been implemented to create a safe and welcoming environment for all children attending the district's child care program. In addition to social distancing measures, Eagle Zone team members received 75 masks created and donated by School Board Chair Elaine Larabee and former School Board Member Jill Scholtz. These important and stylish donations, and the dedication of the Eagle Zone team, are much appreciated. #weareinspired

post_text: Governor Tim Walz announced today that K-12 schools would remain in distance learning. For Eden Prairie Schools, that is through June 9 for K-11 students and June 4 for seniors. Eden Prairie Schools is living out its mission to inspire each student through these unprecedented times. Our teachers and staff will continue to refine distance learning so that each student is supported in personalized learning. We will continue to gather student and family feedback to help us improve and to maintain the educational excellence for which Eden Prairie is known. The success of our schools is due to the tremendous support of our community. Read more at https://www.edenpr.org/experience/news-publications/news/news-details/~board/homepage-news/post/eden-prairie-schools-will-remain-in-distance-learning-the-rest-of-the-school-year

post_text: Gifted & Talented KEY students at Cedar Ridge Elementary participated in the Minnesota Zoo STEM Design Challenge, which included designing an enrichment activity for one of the visually impaired Hawaiian monk seals. On Feb. 6, a representative from the zoo came to judge the exhibits and enrichments. Four groups were invited to the MN Zoo to showcase their designs next month. The zoo staff thought these projects were innovative, well researched and addressed the challenges, needs and considerations of the animals in a unique and creative way. Students in the 3rd-5th grade category will present on March 17, and the 6th-8th grade groups will attend on March 18. #weinspireeach #weareinspired

post_text: ü•™The Sandwich Project ü•™ Second graders at Forest Hills Elementary participated in a philanthropic project to benefit the homeless population in the Twin Cities area today. Allen Law founder of Love One Another came to Forest Hills to talk to the students and collect the sandwiches which he will personally deliver today to those in need. Students learned first hand how community benefits when each person contributes. #corevalues #community #servicelearning #weareinspired #weinspireeach

Eden Prairie Schools recently launched a new mobile-friendly website: www.edenpr.org. You will now be able to directly access the Portal login, staff directory and student life resources (such as school calendars, lunch menus, and transportation). This replaces the Eden Prairie Schools mobile app, which will no longer be offered in app stores. Please delete the app if you still have it on your device, as it is no longer supported.

We encourage you to visit our updated website. You can also save a shortcut for the website (or to a specific page) to your mobile device home screen.
